    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Syringes having an extended tube for intrauterine administration of holy water, refined in the 19th century. The devices were used to baptize a fetus in utero prior to a spontaneous abortion, or when it was othewise feared the unborn infant would die in delivery.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
